$ script-fu.init

`script-fu.init` defines a few interesting functions, such as `(number->string n . base)` that probably aim at making life easier for a â†’ design/graphic/GIMP/Fu/Script[Script-Fu] developer.

{ number->string

  `(number-string n . base)` allows to convert a number to a string with *Script-FU*.
code {
> (number->string 255)
"255"

> (number->string 255 16)
"ff"
code }

}
